# Addon layering

Import DAG: [`backend-architecture-flow.mdc`](backend-architecture-flow.mdc)

## Folder roles

| Folder | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `addon/` | Stremio **`addonBuilder`** wiring |
| `handlers/` | HTTP/Stremio entry — thin orchestration |
| `core/` | Queue, scheduler, prefetch jobs, SSE, room lifecycle |
| `services/` | **`axios`** / streaming I/O; normalize at boundary |
| `factories/` | Pure mappers — no I/O, no `pool.query` |
| `database/` | PostgreSQL SQL — one `pool.query` per function; `withPgTransaction` for multi-step writes |
| `utils/` | Small pure helpers |

## Handlers

- Delegate to lower layers; map errors to responses
- Stremio: `try/catch` → empty safe shapes (`{ streams: [] }`, `{ metas: [] }`)
- Logging: **`dlog`** from **`@/utils/debug.utils`** only

## Database

- One concern per **`*.db.ts`**
- **One `pool.query` per function** (or **`client.query`** inside **`withPgTransaction`**); multi-step writes via **`withPgTransaction`**

## Do not

- Put business orchestration in **`handlers/`** that belongs in **`core/`**
- Duplicate logic — move shared code to the correct layer
